Note=The disease is caused by variants affecting the gene represented in this entry.', 'Glucocorticoid resistance, generalized (GCCR) [MIM', 'Bleeding disorder, platelet-type, 11 (BDPLT11) [MIM', 'Complement factor H deficiency (CFHD) [MIM', 'CFHR5 deficiency (CFHR5D) [MIM', 'Seizures, benign familial infantile, 5 (BFIS5) [MIM', 'Cognitive impairment with or without cerebellar ataxia (CIAT) [MIM', 'Properdin deficiency (PFD) [MIM', 'Macular degeneration, age-related, 4 (ARMD4) [MIM', 'Hemolytic uremic syndrome, atypical, 1 (AHUS1) [MIM', 'Note=Defects in CFHR5 have been found in patients with atypical hemolytic uremic syndrome and may contribute to the disease. Atypical hemolytic uremic syndrome is a complex genetic disease characterized by microangiopathic hemolytic anemia, thrombocytopenia, renal failure and absence of episodes of enterocolitis and diarrhea. In contrast to typical hemolytic uremic syndrome, atypical forms have a poorer prognosis, with higher death rates and frequent progression to end-stage renal disease. Susceptibility to the development of atypical hemolytic uremic syndrome can be conferred by mutations in various components of or regulatory factors in the complement cascade system.
